name: AVAudioSession.ErrorCode
desc: Codes that describe error conditions that may occur when performing audio session operations.

items.name: case none
items.desc: An error code that indicates the operation succeeded.

items.name: case mediaServicesFailed
items.desc: An error code that indictates an attempt to use the audio session during or after a Media Services failure.

items.name: case isBusy
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to deactivate the audio session while it’s still playing or recording.

items.name: case incompatibleCategory
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to perform an operation that the current audio session category doesn’t support.

items.name: case cannotInterruptOthers
items.desc: An error code that indictates an attempt to make a nonmixable audio session active while the app was in the background.

items.name: case missingEntitlement
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to perform an operation for which the app doesn’t have the required entitlements.

items.name: case siriIsRecording
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to perform an operation that isn’t allowed while Siri is recording.

items.name: case cannotStartPlaying
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to start audio playback when it wasn’t allowed.

items.name: case cannotStartRecording
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to start audio recording, but the operation failed.

items.name: case badParam
items.desc: An error code that indicates an attempt to set a property to an illegal value.

items.name: case resourceNotAvailable
items.desc: An error code that indicates that an operation failed because the device doesn’t have sufficient hardware resources to complete the action.

items.name: case unspecified
items.desc: An error code that indicates an unspecified error occurred.

items.name: case expiredSession
items.desc: An error code that indicates that an operation failed because the system deallocated the associated session.

items.name: case sessionNotActive
items.desc: An error code that indicates the operation failed because the session isn’t active.
